## 🐛 Bug Report

<!-- A clear and concise description of what the bug is. -->

Lib version: X.Y.Z

When applying conditional formatting (CF) with mixed or custom icon sets in ExcelJS, the icons do not render correctly in the generated Excel file when using the Streaming XLSX Writer (workbook.xlsx.write() or workbook.xlsx.writeBuffer() with streaming rows).

This issue only occurs in the streaming mode. The same configuration works correctly in the regular (non-streaming) writer.

*****Working Case (Single Icon Set – works fine in streaming):*****

[
  { "iconSet": "5Arrows", "iconId": 4 },
  { "iconSet": "5Arrows", "iconId": 2 },
  { "iconSet": "5Arrows", "iconId": 0 }
]

*******Failing Case (Mixed/Custom Icon Sets – does not render in streaming):******
[
  { "iconSet": "5Arrows", "iconId": 4 },
  { "iconSet": "3TrafficLights1", "iconId": 0 },
  { "iconSet": "3Symbols2", "iconId": 2 }
]

[
  { "iconSet": "NoIcons", "iconId": 0 },
  { "iconSet": "NoIcons", "iconId": 0 },
  { "iconSet": "5Arrows", "iconId": 4 }
]

## Expected Behavior:

Mixed/custom icon sets should render correctly in streaming mode, just like they do in regular mode.

## Actual Behavior:

In streaming mode, when conditional formatting contains multiple icon sets (5Arrows, 3TrafficLights1, 3Symbols2, NoIcons etc.), the icons do not appear in the output file.

## Impact:

This prevents using custom or mixed icon sets in CF when generating large Excel files with the streaming writer.


## Steps To Reproduce

<!-- The exact steps required to reproduce the issue, ideally with a code example -->

```javascript
const ExcelJS = require('exceljs');
const fs = require('fs');

async function run() {
  const workbook = new ExcelJS.stream.xlsx.WorkbookWriter({
    filename: './cf-streaming-issue.xlsx'
  });

  const sheet = workbook.addWorksheet('CF Test');

  // Add sample rows
  sheet.addRow([90]).commit();
  sheet.addRow([60]).commit();
  sheet.addRow([30]).commit();

  // Apply conditional formatting with mixed icon sets
  sheet.addConditionalFormatting({
    ref: 'A1:A3',
    rules: [
      {
        type: 'iconSet',
        iconSet: {
          cfvo: [
            { type: 'num', value: 0 },
            { type: 'num', value: 50 },
            { type: 'num', value: 100 }
          ],
          icons: [
            { iconSet: '5Arrows', iconId: 4 },
            { iconSet: '3TrafficLights1', iconId: 0 },
            { iconSet: '3Symbols2', iconId: 2 }
          ]
        }
      }
    ]
  });

  await workbook.commit();
}

run();

```


